  "substrate_degeneracy_note": "Guided Backprop's defining operation (suppress negative gradients at each ReLU in the backward pass) has no ReLU substrate on the differentiable VCS: its nonlinearities are a distance-softmax (relaxed read), straight-through round/clamp (identity-backward), and a stop-gradient branch — none is a ReLU, and the executed content output is a single linear unit. We report this honestly: Guided BP ≡ rectified saliency here. The suppression rule is verified to be genuinely wired (guided_demo_rectifies provably zeros the negative entries of a mixed-sign surrogate).",
